Widnes Vikings competed in their fourth consecutive [[Super League]] season in 2005 but would be relegated to the [[RFL Championship|National League One]] at the end of an extremely disappointing year for the Vikings. In preparation for the start of the 2005 season they had appointed [[Frank Endacott]], who had previously coached the [[Wigan Warriors]], as well as signing former [[National Rugby League|NRL]] prodigy [[Owen Craigie]] to the club.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hadfield|first1=Dave|title=Widnes name Endacott as coach|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/rugby-league/widnes-name-endacott-as-coach-543850.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220501/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/rugby-league/widnes-name-endacott-as-coach-543850.html |archive-date=2022-05-01 |url-access=subscription|accessdate=6 February 2018|publisher=Independent|date=15 October 2004}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Widnes swoop for Aussie Craigie|url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_league/super_league/widnes/3971605.stm|access-date=6 February 2018|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 November 2004}}</ref> It was hoped that these men could once again lead Widnes to Super League safety once again and bounce back from a dismal 2004 season. While the Vikings managed to finish 11th in the League like last season they were nonetheless relegated due to the pending introduction of the [[Catalans Dragons]] in the 2006 season, they would not return to the top flight until 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fisher|first1=Michael|title=Widnes head for the drop as Briers engineers rout|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/2364136/Widnes-head-for-the-drop-as-Briers-engineers-rout.html|accessdate=6 February 2018|publisher=Telegraph|date=22 August 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Widnes opt against legal action|url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_league/4307410.stm|access-date=6 February 2018|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 October 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Jackson|first1=Andrew|title=Widnes get Super League place as Halifax left in limbo|url=https://www.examiner.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/news/widnes-super-league-place-halifax-4980848|accessdate=6 February 2018|issue=31 March 2011|publisher=Huddersfield Daily Examiner}}</ref>

